    }elseif($count == 8){
        echo '{"categorycounts":{"client features":5,"game contents":8,"major updates":11,"support":3,"useful info":3},"maxeditdate":1513075518,"gamenews":[{"index":0,"id":39,"publishdate":1512460800,"type":"regular","category":"client features","headline":"<p>Quick Looting<\/p>","message":"<center>Use quick looting to loot more efficiently and customise it to your liking.<br \/>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/line1px.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"1\" \/>\n<p>Quick looting allows you to loot all items in a monster corpse with&nbsp;a&nbsp;single click.<\/p>\n<p>If you use Classic Controls, you can choose between the following mouse options to quick loot:<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/quicklooting01.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"503\" height=\"99\" \/><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 52px;\" width=\"556\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 268px; vertical-align: top;\">\n<p>If you use Left Smart-Click, you quick loot all items if you press Alt + left click on a corpse.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 272px; vertical-align: top;\">\n<p>If you use Regular Controls, you quick loot all items if you press Shift + right click on a corpse.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 268px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/quicklooting02.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"91\" height=\"154\" \/><\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 272px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/quicklooting07.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"91\" height=\"154\" \/><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>As a premium player, you can also loot a specific item within a corpse with a single click:<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 30px;\" width=\"608\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 194px; text-align: center;\">Classic Controls<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 194px; text-align: center;\">Left Smart-Click<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 196px; text-align: center;\">Regular Controls<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 194px; text-align: center;\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/quicklooting06.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"179\" height=\"105\" \/><\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 194px; text-align: center;\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/quicklooting03.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"179\" height=\"105\" \/><\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 196px; text-align: center;\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/quicklooting08.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"179\" height=\"105\" \/><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>If you use the animated mouse cursor, a special icon will indicate quick looting. You can activate this cursor in the Options menu.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/quicklooting09.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"327\" height=\"56\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Premium status allows you to refine quick looting with two filters: Skipped Loot and Accepted Loot.<br \/>While you can only use one of the two filters at a time, you can switch between the two of them as you please.<\/p>\n<p>Here\'s how you set them up:<\/p>\n<p>Open the Manage Loot Container dialog. <br \/>You can access it via the Cyclopedia, the context menu of a container or a hotkey which you can assign in the Hotkey section of the Options menu.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/quicklooting10b.png\" width=\"425\" height=\"289\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Choose <em>Skipped Loot<\/em> to exclude certain items from quick looting:<\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 75px; width: 509px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 239px; vertical-align: top;\">(A) You can add an item to your Skipped Loot list via an item\'s context menu. Once added, you can remove that item from the list again via its context menu.<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 254px; vertical-align: top;\">(B) You can also add or remove items via the \"Skip when Quick Looting\" tick box in the Item Cyclopedia.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/quicklooting12.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"513\" height=\"402\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Choose <em>Accepted Loot<\/em> to only quick loot items that you have added to your accepted loot list. You can add an item to your Accepted Loot list or remove it via the item\'s context menu, similar to how it works with the Skipped Loot list.<\/p>\n<p>You can add up to 500 items to both your skipped loot list and your accepted loot list.<br \/>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>How to manage and sort your loot conveniently:<\/p>\n<p>The <em>Manage Loot Container<\/em> dialog allows you to assign categories to your containers to automatically sort quick looted items if you have premium status.<br \/><br \/><\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 102px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 648px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 65px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 411px; height: 65px; vertical-align: middle;\">\n<p>To assign a loot categoy, press the crosshairs button next to it and click on the container of your choice. Done!<\/p>\n<p>From now on, quick looted items of this category will be automatically put into that container.<\/p>\n<p>To remove a loot category from a container, simply press the X button next to the category in the Manage Loot Container dialog.<\/p>\n<p>You can assign multiple categories to the same loot container.<\/p>\n<p>If you hover over the small bag icon in the lower right corner of a container that has at least one category assigned to it, these categories will be displayed.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 205px; height: 65px; vertical-align: middle;\">\n<p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/quicklooting13.png\" width=\"341\" height=\"306\" \/><\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<table style=\"height: 102px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 644px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 65px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 154.5px; height: 65px; vertical-align: middle;\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/quicklooting14.png\" width=\"201\" height=\"136\" \/><\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 459.5px; height: 65px; vertical-align: middle;\">\n<p>Items that belong to categories which you have not assigned to a specific container, will be quick looted into the <em>Unassigned Loot<\/em> container.<\/p>\n<p>Per default, this is your main container, the one you have equipped in&nbsp;the body slot. You can also&nbsp;select a different container for unassigned loot via the Manage Loot Container dialog.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<\/center>","campaignid":0},{"index":1,"id":31,"publishdate":1500962400,"type":"regular","category":"client features","headline":"<p>Analytics Tools<\/p>","message":"<center>Analyse and optimise your hunting sessions by making use of various statistics.<br \/>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/line1px.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"1\" \/>\n<table style=\"height: 153px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 576px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 116px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 297px; height: 116px;\" valign=\"middle\">Click on the respective button below your inventory to access the analytics window in your sidebar. Click the Analyser tools you want to use to open them.<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 247px; height: 116px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/analytics10.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"247\" height=\"161\" \/><\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>Make good use of the additional sidebars you can open on the left and right side of your screen.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/analytics01.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"561\" height=\"257\" \/><\/p>\n<p><br \/><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Hunting Session Analyser<\/span><\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 293px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 605.5px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 198px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 155px; height: 198px;\" valign=\"middle\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/analytics05.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"311\" height=\"311\" \/><\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 328.5px; height: 198px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p>This analyser summarises important values of your current hunting session.<\/p>\n<p>A hunting session starts when you log in, and ends when you log out.<\/p>\n<p>You can start a new session at any time via the small button in the upper right corner. Please note that previously collected data will be discarded and the data in all other Analytics tools will be reset if you start a new hunting session.<\/p>\n<p>You can also copy your session results to your clipboard via this menu to share them with your friends and enemies.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p><br \/><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Drop Tracker<\/span><\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 199px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 652px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 198px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 237.983px; height: 198px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p>It lists all items you have marked for tracking in the Cyclopedia and tells you how many of them you have <span class=\"inline-comment-marker\" data-ref=\"c2e6799c-f71e-4ea0-8cd9-c78c2c0c5475\">looted<\/span> since tracking was started. Click <em>Add Tracked Drop<\/em> to add items via the Cyclopedia.<\/p>\n<p>Free account players can track up to five items at once per character, premium players can track up to 50 items at once per character.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 381.017px; height: 198px;\" valign=\"middle\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/analytics07.png\" width=\"377\" height=\"210\" \/><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>If a monster drops an item you have marked for tracking, you will be notified about it in the drop tracker and the loot channel. Also, a message will pop up at the bottom of the game window.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/analytics08b.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"399\" height=\"241\" \/><\/p>\n<table style=\"width: 724px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 369.817px;\" align=\"center\">As long as the notification is visible in the drop tracker, <br \/>you can hover over it to see when this item dropped.<br \/>If several party members track the same item, all of them will be notified whenever the item is dropped by a monster.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<table style=\"height: 164px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 635px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 198px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 183px; height: 198px;\" valign=\"middle\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/analytics09.png\" width=\"183\" height=\"170\" \/><\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 420px; height: 198px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p>As a premium player, you can also specify a minimum gold value for items you want to have tracked automatically in the drop tracker. Click the small button in the upper right corner of the window to set a value.<\/p>\n<p>If you are already tracking the maximum amount of items (50), newly dropped items that exceed this value will not be displayed in the drop tracker.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p><br \/><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Loot Analyser<\/span><\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 293px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 605.5px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 198px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 155px; height: 198px;\" valign=\"middle\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/analytics03.png\" width=\"353\" height=\"314\" \/><\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 328.5px; height: 198px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p>This analyser allows you to keep track of items looted during your play session&nbsp;and the resulting profit in gold coins based on the NPC price, average Market price on your world or your individually set price.<\/p>\n<p>You can change the loot value source via the Cyclopedia.<\/p>\n<p>If you click on the small button in the upper right corner, you can also set a target value of your choice.<br \/>Use the gauge to track if your current performance is above or below your defined target. Use the graph to see your performance over the last 60 minutes.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p><br \/><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Supply Analyser<\/span><\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 293px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 605.5px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 198px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 155px; height: 198px;\" valign=\"middle\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/analytics02.png\" width=\"369\" height=\"271\" \/><\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 328.5px; height: 198px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p>This analyser shows your current usage of certain <span class=\"inline-comment-marker\" data-ref=\"50080ed1-a057-42a9-9a4b-366c31ad4b4a\">consumable<\/span>s, e.g. potions, runes, or consumed food, and the resulting loss in gold coins based on the NPC price, average Market price on your world or your individually set price.<\/p>\n<p>You can change the loot value source via the Cyclopedia.<\/p>\n<p>If you click on the small button in the upper right corner, you can also set a target value of your choice.<br \/>Use the gauge to track if your current performance is above or below your defined target. Use the graph to see your performance over the last 60 minutes.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p><br \/><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Impact Analyser<\/span><\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 293px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 605.5px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 198px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 155px; height: 198px;\" valign=\"middle\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/analytics04.png\" width=\"289\" height=\"287\" \/><\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 328.5px; height: 198px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p>This analyser shows your current damage and healing performance.<\/p>\n<p>If you click on the small button in the upper right corner, you can choose to display your recent damage or healing values or your average output for the whole session.<br \/>You can also set a target value of your choice via this button. Use the gauge to track if your current performance is above or below your defined target. Use the graph to see your performance over the last 60 minutes.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p><br \/><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">XP Analyser<\/span><\/p>\n<p>This analyser shows your current XP per hour rate and the remaining time to reach the next level.<\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 252px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 627px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 198px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 435px; height: 198px;\" valign=\"middle\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/analytics06.png\" width=\"435\" height=\"258\" \/><\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 160px; height: 198px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p>If you click on the small button in the upper right corner, you can also set a target value of your choice.<br \/>Use the gauge to track if your current performance is above or below your defined target. Use the graph to see your performance over the last 60 minutes.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<\/center>","campaignid":0},{"index":2,"id":28,"publishdate":1497369600,"type":"regular","category":"client features","headline":"<p>Hotkeys<\/p>","message":"<center>Hotkeys allow you to quickly trigger actions by pressing a specific key or key combination. <br \/>Define hotkey presets for your characters to optimise your gameplay!<br \/><table style=\"height: 23px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" width=\"55\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 45px;\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/line1px.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"1\" \/><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>You can have the hotkey preset for a specific character automatically activated upon login.<\/p><p>Press <img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/hotkeys12.png\" width=\"82\" height=\"41\" align=\"middle\" \/> or open the Options menu and go to the Hotkeys section. Check this box:<\/p><table style=\"height: 80px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" width=\"253\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 243px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/hotkeys02.png\" width=\"243\" height=\"84\" \/><\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>Either click <em>Add<\/em> to create a new hotkey preset or <em>Rename<\/em> to change the name an existing one.<\/p><table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; height: 75px;\" width=\"192\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 181px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/hotkeys11.png\" width=\"181\" height=\"52\" \/><\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>Make sure to name the hotkey preset exactly like the character it is meant for and click OK. Done!<\/p><table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; height: 75px;\" width=\"192\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 181px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/hotkeys03.png\" width=\"363\" height=\"164\" \/><\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>&nbsp;<br \/>There are two chat modes in Tibia. This is important to know for your hotkey presets.<\/p><table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 354px; height: 328px;\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 161.917px;\" valign=\"top\"><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Chat On<\/span><\/p><p>You can write text in the chat console.<\/p><p>If you have assigned an action to a letter key (e.g. A), pressing this key will trigger the action but you will not be able to type the letter in the entry line of the chat console.<\/p><\/td><td style=\"width: 160.083px;\" valign=\"top\"><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Chat Off<\/span><\/p><p>You cannot write any text in the entry line of the console.<\/p><p>Per default, you can walk with WASD in this mode.<\/p><\/td><\/tr><tr><td style=\"width: 336px;\" colspan=\"2\" valign=\"top\"><p style=\"text-align: center;\">Chat On*<\/p><p>This temporary mode is a special case. Per default, if you press the Return key in Chat Off mode, it temporarily switches to Chat On* so that you can write one message in the console. As soon as you press Return to send the message, your chat mode will be set to Chat Off again.<\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 593px; height: 128px;\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 403.433px;\" valign=\"middle\">The small button on the right side of the entry line of the chat console tells you which chat mode is currently active. Click it to switch between the two chat modes.<\/td><td style=\"width: 156.567px;\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/hotkeys06a.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"223\" height=\"110\" \/><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>To assign and edit hotkeys, first select the hotkey preset you want to edit.<\/p><table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; height: 195px; width: 304px;\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 359px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/hotkeys05.png\" width=\"359\" height=\"155\" \/><\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>Now select the chat mode for which you want to edit hotkeys via this button:<\/p><table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; height: 42px; width: 285px;\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr style=\"height: 15px;\"><td style=\"width: 274px; height: 15px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/hotkeys04.png\" width=\"274\" height=\"62\" align=\"middle\" \/><\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>If you want your hotkeys to work in both modes, you need to set them in both modes! <br \/>So this basically means that you have to set up your hotkeys twice.<\/p><p>&nbsp;<\/p><table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 377px; height: 76px;\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 239.417px;\" valign=\"middle\">Check this box to get your personal hotkey entries displayed on top of the hotkey list.<\/td><td style=\"width: 104.583px;\" valign=\"middle\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/hotkeys07.png\" width=\"117\" height=\"53\" align=\"middle\" \/><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>You can either assign a text message or an object to a hotkey.<\/p><table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; height: 179px; width: 653px;\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr style=\"height: 21px;\"><td style=\"width: 269.983px; height: 21px;\" valign=\"middle\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/hotkeys08.png\" width=\"267\" height=\"157\" \/><\/p><\/td><td style=\"width: 351.017px; height: 21px;\" valign=\"middle\"><p>(1) Click on the red line <em>Add new entry...<\/em><\/p><p>(2) If you click <em>Edit hotkey text<\/em>, you can enter a text message, e.g. magic words to cast a spell.<br \/>If you check the box <em>Send automatically<\/em>, the message will be sent immediately when you press the assigned hotkey.<\/p><p>If you click <em>Edit hotkey object<\/em>, your mouse cursor will turn into a crosshair. Click on the item of your choice and choose your preferred action.<\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; height: 197px; width: 778px;\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr style=\"height: 121px;\"><td style=\"width: 389px; height: 121px;\" valign=\"top\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/hotkeys09.png\" width=\"389\" height=\"256\" \/><\/td><td style=\"width: 357px; height: 121px;\" valign=\"middle\"><p>After you have added a new entry, you need to assign a hotkey to it by clicking in the field <em>First Key<\/em>.<\/p><p>This will open a window where you can edit the hotkey. <br \/>Press the key or key combination of your choice and click OK to assign the hotkey and close this window.<\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>&nbsp;You can assign up to 2 hotkeys to every action. You need to have a hotkey assigned in the column <em>First Key<\/em> to be able to assign a hotkey in the column <em>Second Key<\/em>.<\/p><p>&nbsp;<\/p><p>Always remember to save your hotkey changes and settings before closing the hotkey dialog! <br \/>To do so you can either click Apply to save your changes or click OK to save your changes and close the dialog.<\/p><table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/hotkeys10.png\" width=\"171\" height=\"56\" \/><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>&nbsp;<\/p><p>How to assign a hotkey to toggle between Chat On an Off:<\/p><table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; height: 140px; width: 470px;\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr style=\"height: 121px;\"><td style=\"width: 452px; height: 121px;\" valign=\"top\"><ul><li>Set <em>hotkey preset for chat mode<\/em> to Chat Off, scroll to the predefined action <em>Chat Mode: Set to Chat On<\/em>. Assign the hotkey of your choice.<\/li><\/ul><ul><li>Set <em>hotkey preset for chat mode<\/em> to Chat On, scroll to the predefined action <em>Chat Mode: Set to Chat Off<\/em>. Assign the same hotkey.<\/li><\/ul><ul><li>Click Apply to save or OK to save and close the hotkey dialog. Pressing this hotkey now toggles between the chat modes.<\/li><\/ul><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/center>","campaignid":0},{"index":3,"id":26,"publishdate":1497348000,"type":"regular","category":"client features","headline":"<p>Action Bars<\/p>","message":"<center><\/center><center>Make use of the buttons in your action bar to quickly trigger actions or messages.<br \/><table style=\"height: 23px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" width=\"55\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 45px;\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/line1px.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"1\" \/><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>Action bars are displayed below your game window. <br \/>Right-click on an action button to assign a spell, object, text or hotkey to it.<\/p><table style=\"height: 105px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" width=\"110\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 173px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/actionbars02.png\" width=\"173\" height=\"103\" \/><\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>&nbsp;<\/p><table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; height: 317px; width: 607px;\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr style=\"height: 241px;\"><td style=\"width: 245.667px; height: 241px;\" valign=\"top\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/actionbars03.png\" width=\"182\" height=\"200\" \/><\/td><td style=\"width: 329.333px; height: 241px;\" valign=\"top\"><p>(1) Click on <em>Assign Spell<\/em> to open a small window listing the various spells. Select a spell.<\/p><p>(2) Click OK to assign it to the action button. You can now trigger the spell by clicking on this button in your action bar.<\/p><p>You can also open the spell list window via the control buttons below your inventory to assign a spell by dragging and dropping it on an action button.<\/p><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/actionbars04.png\" width=\"245\" height=\"119\" \/><\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>&nbsp;<\/p><p>If you select <em>Assign Object, <\/em>your mouse cursor will turn into a crosshair.<\/p><table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; height: 350px; width: 722px;\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 427px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/actionbars05.png\" width=\"427\" height=\"306\" \/><\/p><\/td><td style=\"width: 263px;\" valign=\"top\"><p>&nbsp;<\/p><p>Click on an item to assign it to the action button. Choose your preferred action in the window that will pop up.<\/p><p>&nbsp;<\/p><p>You can also drag&amp;drop an item on an action button to assign it.<\/p><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/actionbars06.png\" width=\"181\" height=\"65\" align=\"right\" \/><\/p><p>&nbsp;<\/p><p>&nbsp;<\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>&nbsp;<\/p><table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; height: 266px; width: 525px;\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr style=\"height: 158px;\"><td style=\"width: 321px; height: 158px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/actionbars07.png\" width=\"321\" height=\"230\" \/><\/p><\/td><td style=\"width: 172px; height: 158px;\" valign=\"top\"><p>(1) Click on <em>Assign Text<\/em> to open a small window where you can enter text.<\/p><p>(2) Click OK to assign the text to this action button. If you want to send the text right away when clicking the action button, select <em>send automatically <\/em>before hitting OK.<\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>&nbsp;<\/p><p>You can also assign a hotkey to an action button to trigger it via this key.<\/p><table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; height: 327px; width: 792px;\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr style=\"height: 190px;\"><td style=\"width: 466.367px; height: 190px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/actionbars08.png\" width=\"447\" height=\"284\" \/><\/p><\/td><td style=\"width: 292.633px; height: 190px;\" valign=\"middle\"><p>(1) Click on <em>Assign Hotkey<\/em> to open this window. Press the key or key combination you want to assign.<\/p><p>(2) Click OK to assign the hotkey to this action button. The hotkey will be displayed in the upper right corner of the action button.<\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>&nbsp;<\/p><p>Use the small arrow buttons on the left and right side of an action bar to navigate through it.<\/p><table style=\"height: 31px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 530px;\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr style=\"height: 45px;\"><td style=\"width: 43.8167px; height: 45px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/actionbars09.png\" vspace=\"4\" width=\"31\" height=\"36\" align=\"right\" \/><\/p><\/td><td style=\"width: 454.183px; height: 45px;\"><p>Clicking the small lock on the right allows you to lock or unlock the ability to assign actions via drag&amp;drop.<\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>&nbsp;<\/p><p>You can adjust your general action bar settings via the Options menu. You can have up to two action bars with 50 action buttons per bar.<\/p><table style=\"height: 38px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" width=\"224\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr style=\"height: 45px;\"><td style=\"width: 207px; height: 45px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/actionbars01.png\" width=\"419\" height=\"128\" \/><\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/center>","campaignid":0},{"index":4,"id":2,"publishdate":1497020400,"type":"regular","category":"client features","headline":"<p>Battle List<\/p>","message":"<center>The battle list shows all characters and monsters in your current battle range. <br \/>Use it to attack your targets accurately!<br \/><table style=\"height: 23px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" width=\"55\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 45px;\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/line1px.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"1\" \/><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>Press <img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/battlelist07com.png\" alt=\"hotkey\" width=\"83\" height=\"42\" align=\"middle\" \/> or click the battle list button to open the battle list in your sidebar:<\/p><table style=\"height: 150px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" width=\"168\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 253px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/battlelist01com.png\" alt=\"button\" width=\"253\" height=\"109\" \/><\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>&nbsp;<\/p><p>Battle list filters allow you to show or hide members of five different groups: <br \/>players, NPCs, monsters, non-skulled players, and party members.<\/p><table style=\"height: 39px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" width=\"193\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 183px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/battlelist02com.png\" alt=\"filters\" width=\"377\" height=\"124\" align=\"middle\" \/><\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>&nbsp;<\/p><p>You can also sort the creatures shown in your battle list by certain critera.<\/p><table style=\"height: 27px; width: 383px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 56px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/battlelist04com.png\" alt=\"sorting\" width=\"373\" height=\"187\" \/><\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>&nbsp;<\/p><p>Left-click on a creature to attack, right-click on it to open the context menu with further options.<\/p><table style=\"height: 27px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" width=\"57\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 47px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/battlelist05b.png\" alt=\"menu\" width=\"265\" height=\"291\" \/><\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>&nbsp;<\/p><p>If you press Spacebar in Chat Off mode, you will attack the next target in your battle list. <br \/>You can also set your own hotkey for this.<\/p><table style=\"height: 26px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" width=\"34\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 24px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/battlelist06b.png\" alt=\"spacebar\" width=\"231\" height=\"110\" \/><\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/center>","campaignid":0},{"index":0,"id":40,"publishdate":1512460800,"type":"regular","category":"game contents","headline":"<p>Bestiary and Charms<\/p>","message":"<center>Gather useful details about Tibian creatures in the Bestiary to unlock hunting benefits.<br \/>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/line1px.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"1\" \/>\n<p>You can access the Bestiary via the respective tab in the Tibia Cyclopedia.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/bestiary01.png\" width=\"411\" height=\"271\" \/><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 52px; width: 554px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 343.5px; vertical-align: middle;\">\n<p>Here, you can see various creature classes in Tibia, the total number of creatures in each class and how many of them you have already killed at least once.<\/p>\n<p>Click on a class to see all creatures within that class.<\/p>\n<p>A creature is considered unknown to you if you have not killed it at least once after the winter update 2017.&nbsp;<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 196.5px; text-align: left; vertical-align: middle;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/bestiary02.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"129\" height=\"121\" \/><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>Unknown creatures appear as shadows. As soon as you kill a creature for the first time, it will be displayed with its name and in colour and you can click on it to see details about it.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/bestiary03.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"431\" height=\"351\" \/>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 52px; width: 554px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 343.5px; vertical-align: middle;\">\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>On a creature\'s detailed page, you can see its difficulty level and a kill counter which&nbsp;tells you how many times you need to kill this creature to unlock further details.<\/p>\n<p>The number of kills you need to unlock each of the three stages of detail, depends on a creature\'s difficulty level.<\/p>\n<p>Unlocking the third stage of detail completes a creature\'s entry. It now provides&nbsp;a wealth of information about the creature, ranging from basic stats to elemental sensitivities and loot drops, for example.<\/p>\n<p>Speaking of loot: If a creature drops very rare loot items, they will only be displayed if you have completed the creature\'s entry and looted the item at least once.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 196.5px; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/bestiary04.png\" width=\"199\" height=\"94\" \/><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>Completing a creature\'s entry will be rewarded with charm points which you can spend&nbsp;to unlock&nbsp;charms - various offensive, defensive or passive bonus effects.<\/p>\n<p>You can check all available charms and their prices in the Charms tab in the Cyclopedia.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/bestiary05.png\" width=\"353\" height=\"271\" \/><\/p>\n<p>The number of charm points you receive for completing a creature\'s entry depends on&nbsp;the creature\'s&nbsp;difficulty level.<\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 79px;\" width=\"215\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 205px;\">\n<ul>\n<li>Trivial: 5 charm points<\/li>\n<li>Easy: 15 charm&nbsp;points<\/li>\n<li>Medium: 25 charm&nbsp;points<\/li>\n<li>Hard: 50 charm&nbsp;points<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>How to unlock a charm:<\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 297px; width: 631px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 246px; vertical-align: middle;\">\n<p>1) Collect enough charm points to unlock the charm of your choice.<\/p>\n<p>2) Go to the Charms tab and click on the charm to select it.<\/p>\n<p>3) Unlock it by clicking the respective button.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>Unlocked charms can be assigned to creatures with completed entries in the Bestiary.<\/p>\n<p>A charm can only be used against one creature at a time. Also, a creature can only have one charm assigned at a time.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 353px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/bestiary06.png\" width=\"353\" height=\"271\" \/><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p><br \/>You can assign charms via the Charms tab or directly on a creature\'s completed Bestiary page.<\/p>\n<p>Via the Charms tab:<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/bestiary07.png\" width=\"573\" height=\"224\" \/><\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 114px;\" width=\"497\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 109px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 487px; height: 109px;\">\n<p>1) Click on the charm you want to assign.&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>2) Click on the creature against which you want to use the charm. You can only select creatures with completed entries and which do not have a charm assigned at the moment.&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>3) Click Select to assign the charm to this creature.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>Via a completed creature page:<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/bestiary08.png\" width=\"509\" height=\"318\" \/><\/p>\n&nbsp;\n<table style=\"height: 95px;\" width=\"398\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 388px;\">\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>1) Use the drop down menu and click on the charm you want to assign. You can only select unlocked charms which are currently not assigned to a creature.<\/p>\n<p>2) Click on the charm you want to use against this creature.&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>3) Click Select to assign the charm to this creature.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>If you want to use an assigned charm against a different creature or if you want to assign a different charm to a creature that is already linked to a charm, you can remove the charm for a gold fee via the Charms tab or on the creature\'s Bestiary page.<\/p>\n<p>Premium players can assign up to six charms to different creatures at the same time, while free accounts can assign up to two.&nbsp;The Store allows you to purchase the permanent ability to assign all of your unlocked charms at the same time. It also reduces the amount of gold you have to pay for every charm removal by 25%.<\/p>\n<\/center>","campaignid":0},{"index":1,"id":36,"publishdate":1506517200,"type":"regular","category":"game contents","headline":"<p>The Market<\/p>","message":"<center>The Market allows you to trade items and Tibia Coins with other players.<br \/>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/line1px.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"1\" \/>\n<p>Open the Market by by clicking on the respective button in your depot locker.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/market01.png\" width=\"377\" height=\"359\" \/><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 102px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 648px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 83px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 89px; height: 83px;\" valign=\"top\">\n<p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/market02.png\" width=\"89\" height=\"241\" align=\"right\" \/><\/p>\n<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 527px; height: 83px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p>Browse through the various categories (1) or use the search (2) to find the item you are interested in.<\/p>\n<p>Select an item in the object list below Categories to see its current sell and buy offers sorted by the piece price.<\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 18px; width: 525px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 216px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 220.5px; height: 216px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p><br \/>The average item prices are calculated on a daily basis for each game world.<\/p>\n<p>Sell offers that are 25 % or more above a game world\'s average price are displayed in <strong style=\"color: #e06757;\">red<\/strong>, as are buy offers that are 25 % or more below the average.<\/p>\n<p>If you lack the money or items to accept a sell or buy offer, this offer will be greyed out.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 280px; height: 216px;\" valign=\"middle\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/market03.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"279\" height=\"183\" \/><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>For more details on the selected item, including trading statistics of the last 30 days, click on the <em>Details<\/em> button in the lower right corner of the Market window.<\/p>\n<center>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/market04.png\" width=\"325\" height=\"198\" \/><\/center>\n<p><br \/>How to create a SELL offer:<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/market06.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"577\" height=\"108\" \/><\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 123px; width: 540px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 19px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 699px; height: 19px;\" colspan=\"2\">\n<p><br \/>1) Select an item and click <em>Sell<\/em> in the <em>Create Offer<\/em> section. You can only sell items that are stored in your depot chest.<br \/>2) Enter the <em>Piece Price <\/em>you want to charge for one unit of the item you are about to offer.<br \/>3) Select the number of item units you want to sell via the slider <em>Amount<\/em>. To increase the slider\'s step size, hold Shift, Ctrl or Shift+Ctrl while using the slider.<br \/>4) Tick the box <em>Anonymous<\/em> if you do not want to reveal that you are the creator of this offer.<br \/>5) If you have entered everything correctly, click on <em>Create<\/em> to place the offer.<\/p>\n<p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/market05.png\" hspace=\"10\" width=\"299\" height=\"65\" align=\"right\" \/><\/p>\n<p>You can only place a sell offer if you have enough gold to pay the fee. Hover over your balance in the lower left corner of the Market window to see how much you have in cash and in your bank account.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p><br \/>How to accept a SELL offer to buy something from someone else:<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/market09.png\" width=\"573\" height=\"76\" \/><\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 45px; width: 549px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 19px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 539px; height: 19px;\">\n<p><br \/>1) Select an item and click on the offer of your choice in the <em>Sell Offers<\/em> list. <br \/>2) Set the number of item units you want to buy via the slider <em>Amount<\/em>. <br \/>3) Check the total amount you will have to pay and click on <em>Accept<\/em> to seal the deal.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p><br \/>How to create a BUY offer:<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/market07.png\" width=\"577\" height=\"108\" \/><\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 123px; width: 540px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 19px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 500px; height: 19px;\">\n<p><br \/>1) Select an item and click <em>Buy<\/em> in the <em>Create Offer<\/em> section. You can only place a buy offer if you have enough gold to pay the fee and your offered price.<br \/>2) Enter the <em>Piece Price<\/em> you are willing to spend on one unit of the item you want to buy. <br \/>3) Select the number of item units you want to buy via the slider <em>Amount<\/em>. To increase the slider\'s step size, hold Shift, Ctrl or Shift+Ctrl while using the slider.<br \/>4) Tick the box <em>Anonymous<\/em> if you do not want others to know that you are the creator of this offer. <br \/>5) If you have entered everything correctly, click on <em>Create<\/em> to place the offer.<\/p>\n<p>Items from the Market will be transferred directly to your mail inbox which you access via your depot locker.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>How to accept a BUY offer to sell something to someone else:<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/market08.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"573\" height=\"76\" \/><\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 61px; width: 532px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 19px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 522px; height: 19px;\">\n<p><br \/>1) Select an item and click on the offer of your choice in the <em>Buy Offers<\/em> list. You can only sell items that are stored in your depot chest.<br \/>2) Set the number of item units you want to sell via the slider <em>Amount<\/em>. <br \/>3) Check the total amount you will earn and click on <em>Accept<\/em> to seal the deal.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>Check the section <em>My Offers<\/em> to get an overview of your current offers and your offer history.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/market10.png\" width=\"325\" height=\"28\" \/><\/p>\n<\/center>","campaignid":0},{"index":2,"id":35,"publishdate":1506513600,"type":"regular","category":"game contents","headline":"<p>Depot Chest and Inboxes<\/p>","message":"<center>Depots can be found in all major cities in Tibia. Visit them to access your stored items.<br \/>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/line1px.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"1\" \/>\n<p>Click on a locker in a depot to open your character\'s personal depot locker. It contains your depot chest, your inbox, and grants you access to the Market.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/depotchest01.png\" width=\"249\" height=\"93\" \/><br \/><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><br \/><\/span><\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 159px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 636px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 81px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 198px; height: 81px;\" valign=\"top\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/depotchest02.png\" width=\"179\" height=\"316\" \/><\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 959.133px; height: 81px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Depot Chest and Depot Boxes<\/span><\/p>\n<p>Click on the depot chest in your locker to open it. You can access your depot chest from any depot, no matter in which city you currently are.<\/p>\n<p>It contains 17 numbered depot boxes in which you can store your items.<\/p>\n<p>If you are a free account player you can store up to 2,000 items in your depot chest. Premium players are allowed to store a maximum of 10,000 items.<\/p>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Tibia History Snippet<\/span><\/p>\n<p>Until December 2015, each city had its own depot chest which you could only access from the city\'s depot. With the winter update 2015, we introduced the <a href=\"http:\/\/www.tibia.com\/news\/?subtopic=newsarchive&amp;id=3369\" target=\"_blank\">global depot<\/a> and thus, the depot chest of each city turned into a numbered depot box inside the global depot chest.<\/p>\n<p>If you are looking for items you had stored in a city depot before that update, simply check its corresponding depot box. You can find out its number in the list to the right.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 72.8667px; height: 81px;\" valign=\"bottom\">\n<table style=\"height: 17px; width: 139.367px;\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"2\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 15px;\">\n<th style=\"width: 80px; height: 15px;\">Former <br \/>City Depot<\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 42.3667px; height: 15px;\">Box #<\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 15px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 80px; height: 15px;\">Thais<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 42.3667px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;I<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 15px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 80px; height: 15px;\">Carlin<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 42.3667px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;II<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 15px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 80px; height: 15px;\">Kazordoon<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 42.3667px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;III<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 15px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 80px; height: 15px;\">Ab\'Dendriel<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 42.3667px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;IV<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 15px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 80px; height: 15px;\">Edron<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 42.3667px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;V<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 15px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 80px; height: 15px;\">Darashia<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 42.3667px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;VI<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 15px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 80px; height: 15px;\">Venore<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 42.3667px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;VII<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 15px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 80px; height: 15px;\">Ankrahmun<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 42.3667px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;VIII<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 15px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 80px; height: 15px;\">Port Hope<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 42.3667px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;IX<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 15px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 80px; height: 15px;\">Liberty Bay<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 42.3667px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;X<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 15px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 80px; height: 15px;\">Svargrond<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 42.3667px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;XI<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 15px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 80px; height: 15px;\">Yalahar<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 42.3667px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;XII<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 15px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 80px; height: 15px;\">Travora<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 42.3667px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;XIII<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 15px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 80px; height: 15px;\">Farmine<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 42.3667px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;XIV<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 15px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 80px; height: 15px;\">Gray Beach<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 42.3667px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;XV<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 15px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 80px; height: 15px;\">Roshamuul<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 42.3667px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;XVI<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 15px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 80px; height: 15px;\">Rathleton<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 42.3667px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;XVII<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 10px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 198px; height: 10px;\" valign=\"top\">&nbsp;<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 959.133px; height: 10px;\" valign=\"middle\">&nbsp;<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 72.8667px; height: 10px;\" valign=\"bottom\">&nbsp;<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<table style=\"height: 102px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 648px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 65px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 438.333px; height: 65px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Inbox and Store Inbox<\/span><\/p>\n<p>Click on the mailbox in your locker to acces your inbox. If you have received any parcels or letters, they will arrive here.<\/p>\n<p>Also, if you have lost a house, your items will be transferred to your inbox. Further, all items you have bought via the Market will arrive in your inbox.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 175.667px; height: 65px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/depotchest03.png\" width=\"179\" height=\"184\" \/><\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<table style=\"height: 102px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 648px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 65px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 325.5px; height: 65px;\" valign=\"middle\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/store11.png\" width=\"341\" height=\"167\" \/><\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 290.5px; height: 65px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p>Please note that your mail inbox is different from your Store Inbox.<\/p>\n<p>The Store inbox contains portable items you have bought in the Store or received as daily reward. You can open the Store inbox wherever you are by clicking on this small button next to your inventory.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<\/center>","campaignid":0},{"index":3,"id":30,"publishdate":1500962400,"type":"regular","category":"game contents","headline":"<p>Daily Rewards<\/p>","message":"<center>Pick up daily rewards for your character and enjoy certain bonuses if you do so on consecutive days.<br \/>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/line1px.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"1\" \/><\/center><center>\n<p>Reward shrines can be found in the temples of all major cities in Tibia and in the Adventurers\' Guild.<\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 202px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 637px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 198px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 238.5px; height: 198px;\" valign=\"middle\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/dailyreward01.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"283\" height=\"380\" \/><\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 365.5px; height: 198px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p>Use a reward shrine to open the reward wall and collect your reward directly for free.<br \/><br \/><\/p>\n<table style=\"width: 322px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 267px;\">You can also click the reward wall button below your inventory to open it wherever you are. <br \/>In this case, though, you can only pick up your reward if you use an <em>Instant Reward Access<\/em>, which you can buy in the Store.<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 39px;\" align=\"right\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/dailyreward02.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"29\" height=\"56\" \/><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>You can also purchase a reward shrine for your own four walls in the Store. Unwrap it in your house to be able to collect your daily reward from there.<\/p>\n<p>If you have premium status, you will receive better rewards and are able to unlock more bonuses if you collect them on consecutive days. <br \/>Simply hover over a reward for further info on its free and premium version.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>This is the reward lane:<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/dailyreward03.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"509\" height=\"135\" \/><\/p>\n<p>It shows the rewards and the order in which you will be able to claim them during one reward cycle.<\/p>\n<p>To advance in the reward lane, you need to pick up the reward that is currently available for you. <br \/>Once you have reached and claimed the final reward, a new reward cycle will start which means you will start at the beginning of the reward lane again.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/dailyreward04.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"509\" height=\"135\" \/><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<table style=\"width: 413px; height: 97px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 306px;\" valign=\"middle\">If you have collected a reward, check the timer below the next reward to see when you will be able to claim it.<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px;\" valign=\"middle\">&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/dailyreward05.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"75\" height=\"101\" \/><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<table style=\"width: 475px; height: 162px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 303px;\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/dailyreward06.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"303\" height=\"162\" \/><\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 140px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p>Rewards that are objects (e.g. potions) are directly delivered to your Store Inbox. Please note that some items expire if not used within a certain time frame. Just click on an item to look at it for further info.<\/p>\n<p>You can access your Store inbox via this button:<\/p>\n<p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/store11.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"341\" height=\"167\" \/><\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>If a reward can be collected, check the box below it to see if it costs you an Instant Reward Access to pick it up directly:<\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 391px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 636px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 209px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 302px; height: 209px;\" valign=\"top\">If you open the reward wall via a reward shrine, you can claim your reward for free:<br \/><br \/><center>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/dailyreward09.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"157\" height=\"228\" \/><\/center><\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 302px; height: 209px;\" valign=\"top\">If you open the reward wall via the respective button, a 1 is displayed below the reward which means you need&nbsp;an Instant Reward Access to collect this reward directly. <br \/><center>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/dailyreward10.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"181\" height=\"235\" \/><\/center>\n<p>In the lower left corner of the reward wall, you can check the number of Instant Reward Access currently available to you. If you do not have any left, click on the button next to that info box to open the Store and buy some with Tibia Coins.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>Pick up your reward on consecutive days to unlock special bonuses in resting areas such as regeneration of hitpoints, mana, stamina or soulpoints.<\/p>\n<p>This is your reward streak:<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/dailyreward11.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"551\" height=\"107\" \/><\/p>\n<p>(1) Here you can see on how many days in a row you have collected your reward. As long as you pick up your daily reward once during each server cycle, your reward streak will increase. A server cycle is the time between two regular server saves.<\/p>\n<p>(2) Hover over the dragons to get further info on currently unlocked bonuses and those you will unlock if your reward streak increases.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 115px; width: 579px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 414.35px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p>You will keep all your unlocked bonuses as long as you do not break your reward streak.<\/p>\n<p>Check the reward wall to see how much time you have left in the current server cycle to pick up your reward without breaking your reward streak. Once you have collected your reward for the current server cycle, a green check mark will appear.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 131.65px;\" valign=\"middle\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/dailyreward08.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"201\" height=\"97\" \/><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>&nbsp;If you miss to collect your reward during a server cycle, your reward streak will be reset to the first bonus as soon as you pick up your next daily reward.<\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 210px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 571px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 198px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 407.767px; height: 198px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p>Where to find resting areas?<\/p>\n<p>Resting areas can be found in the temples of all major cities, in the Adventurers\' Guild, in player houses and in most depots.<\/p>\n<p>Whenever you are in a resting area, a special status icon will appear beneath your inventory. Hover your mouse cursor over it to check your active bonuses.<\/p>\n<p>Keep in mind that you need to eat something for regeneration bonuses to work.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 130.233px; height: 198px;\" valign=\"middle\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/dailyreward07.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"205\" height=\"178\" \/><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<\/center>","campaignid":0},{"index":4,"id":34,"publishdate":1500955200,"type":"regular","category":"game contents","headline":"<p>Item Cyclopedia<\/p>","message":"<center>The&nbsp;Item Cyclopedia provides useful information about most tradable items in Tibia.<br \/>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/line1px.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"1\" \/>\n<p>Click on the respective button below your inventory to open the Tibia Cyclopedia.&nbsp;You now see the Items section.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/cyclopedia01_12.png\" width=\"411\" height=\"271\" \/><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 346px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 635px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 100px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 191.817px; height: 100px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/cyclopedia02b.png\" width=\"217\" height=\"363\" \/><\/p>\n<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 578.183px; height: 100px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p>Browse through the various categories (1) or use the search function (2) to find the item you are interested in.<\/p>\n<p>Click on an item to get further details such as the description and stats of the item, as well as info on NPCs buying or selling this item for which price and where. In addition, you will also see the average Market price of this item on your game world.<\/p>\n<center>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/cyclopedia03c.png\" width=\"364\" height=\"221\" \/><\/center><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<table style=\"height: 100px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 635px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 19px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 150.55px; height: 19px;\" valign=\"top\">\n<p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/cyclopedia04b.png\" width=\"173\" height=\"61\" \/><\/p>\n<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 618.45px; height: 19px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p>You can choose whether the NPC buy value or the average Market value should be used for item price calculations in various analytics tools.<\/p>\n<p>If you have premium status, you can also set your own loot&nbsp;value for each item.<\/p>\n<center><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/cyclopedia05b.png\" width=\"353\" height=\"28\" \/><\/center><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>If you have selected an item and check this box, the item will be tracked during your character\'s hunting session.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/cyclopedia06b.png\" width=\"187\" height=\"54\" \/><\/p>\n<p>For more information on item tracking, check the Compendium entry about <em>Analytics Tools<\/em> under Client Features.<\/p>\n<p>You can also add an item to your skipped loot list if you check this box.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/cyclopedia07_12.png\" width=\"189\" height=\"53\" \/><\/p>\n<p>For more information on skipped loot, check the Compendium entry about&nbsp;<em>Quick Looting<\/em>&nbsp;under Client Features.<\/p>\n<\/center>","campaignid":0},{"index":5,"id":33,"publishdate":1500955200,"type":"regular","category":"game contents","headline":"<p>Quest Tracker<\/p>","message":"<center>Track your quest progress via the quest tracker in your sidebar.<br \/>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/line1px.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"1\" \/><\/center><center>\n<table style=\"height: 202px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 637px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 198px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 238.5px; height: 198px;\" valign=\"middle\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/questtracker01.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"325\" height=\"217\" \/><\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 365.5px; height: 198px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p>Open your quest log via the respective button and click on <em>Quest Tracker<\/em> in the lower left corner to <span class=\"inline-comment-marker\" data-ref=\"e38ba02f-26e7-4a61-aa83-50504155be49\">open it<\/span> in your sidebar.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>Here is how to add a quest to the quest tracker:<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/questtracker02.png\" width=\"609\" height=\"206\" \/><\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 118px;\" width=\"541\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 523px; height: 65px;\" valign=\"middle\">(1) Open your quest log via the respective button or by clicking <em>Add Tracked Quest<\/em> in the Quest Tracker.<br \/>(2) Go to the quest of your choice, e.g. <em>Killing in the name of...<\/em>, and select the task or mission you would like to track.<br \/>(3) Check the small box to add it to your quest tracker. <br \/><center>Now you can easily follow the progress you make on this quest without having to open your quest log.<\/center><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<table style=\"height: 102px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 648px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 65px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 411px; height: 65px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p>To remove a quest from the quest tracker, right-click on its entry (1) and select <em>Remove<\/em> (2). You can also remove all currently tracked entries at once via a menu that will open if you click on the small button in the upper right corner(3).<\/p>\n<p>Free account players can track up to five quests at once per character, premium players can track up to 20 quests at once per character.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 205px; height: 65px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/questtracker03.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"205\" height=\"139\" \/><\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<table style=\"height: 102px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 648px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 65px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 325.5px; height: 65px;\" valign=\"middle\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/questtracker04.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"323\" height=\"81\" \/><\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 290.5px; height: 65px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p>Hover over an entry in the quest tracker to see the name of the questline and the task or mission.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<\/center>","campaignid":0},{"index":6,"id":23,"publishdate":1497268800,"type":"regular","category":"game contents","headline":"<p>Prey<\/p>","message":"<center>Activate a prey to gain a bonus when hunting certain monsters!<br \/><table style=\"height: 23px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" width=\"55\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 45px;\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/line1px.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"1\" \/><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>Press <img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/prey07.png\" width=\"83\" height=\"42\" align=\"middle\" \/> to open the prey dialog.<\/p><p>&nbsp;<\/p><table style=\"height: 122px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 450px;\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 256px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/prey01.png\" width=\"256\" height=\"84\" \/><\/p><\/td><td style=\"width: 162px;\"><p>(1) You can also click the prey button to open the prey window in your sidebar.<\/p><p>(2) Left-click in the prey window to open the prey dialog.<\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><br \/><table style=\"height: 201px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 712px;\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr style=\"height: 162px;\"><td style=\"width: 270.55px; vertical-align: top; height: 162px;\"><p>Select your prey or click here if you want to reroll the monsters to choose from:<\/p><\/td><td style=\"width: 97.45px; height: 162px; vertical-align: top;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/prey02.png\" hspace=\"10\" width=\"119\" height=\"151\" \/><\/p><\/td><td style=\"width: 297px; vertical-align: top; height: 162px;\"><p>You get a free list reroll every 20 hours. The gold price for a list reroll depends on your character level.<\/p><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/prey04.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"215\" height=\"104\" \/><\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>&nbsp;<\/p><table style=\"height: 182px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 615px;\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 193.433px;\" valign=\"top\">If you have selected your prey, click here to activate it and get a random bonus: damage boost, damage reduction, bonus XP, or improved loot.<\/td><td style=\"width: 130.567px;\" valign=\"top\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/prey03.png\" width=\"121\" height=\"153\" \/><\/p><\/td><td style=\"width: 244px;\" valign=\"top\">You can reroll your bonus to get one with a higher value (max. 50%). Bonus Rerolls can be purchased for Tibia Coins in the Store.<p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/prey05.png\" width=\"215\" height=\"104\" \/><\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>&nbsp;<\/p><table style=\"height: 204px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 831px;\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr style=\"height: 109px;\"><td style=\"width: 399.5px; vertical-align: top; height: 109px;\"><p>You want a different prey but would like to keep your current bonus?<\/p><p>Roll for a new monster list while you already have an active prey. Select a new prey from the list and activate it. Your hunting time will be reset to 2 hours.<\/p><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/prey08.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"229\" height=\"79\" \/><\/p><\/td><td style=\"width: 399.5px; vertical-align: top; height: 109px;\"><p>You want a different bonus but would like to keep your current prey?<\/p><p>Roll for a new bonus while you already have an active prey. Your hunting time will be reset to 2 hours with your new bonus.<\/p><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/prey09.png\" width=\"228\" height=\"79\" \/><\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>&nbsp;<\/p><p>The prey window shows your current prey, your bonus and the remaining time for the prey. <br \/>Hover over your prey for a tooltip with details.<\/p><table style=\"height: 68px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 145px;\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 177px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/prey06.png\" width=\"177\" height=\"70\" \/><\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>By the way: Prey time only decreases while hunting!<\/p><table style=\"height: 23px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" width=\"55\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 45px;\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/line1px.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"1\" \/><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>You can activate up to 3 preys simultaneously. <br \/>All players can use the first prey slot, Premium players can also use the second slot. Additional prey slots can be unlocked permanently by purchasing them for Tibia Coins in the Store.<\/p><\/center>","campaignid":0},{"index":7,"id":22,"publishdate":1497265200,"type":"regular","category":"game contents","headline":"<p>Imbuing<\/p>","message":"<center>Imbuing allows you to temporarily boost your equipment!<br \/>\n<table style=\"height: 23px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" width=\"55\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 45px;\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/line1px.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"1\" \/><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 139px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 400px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 326.2px;\" valign=\"middle\">Visit Albinius north of Thais, collect heavy old tomes for him and hand them over via the key word <em>temple<\/em> to unlock the ability to use imbuing shrines.<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 10px;\">\n<p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/imbuing01.png\" width=\"107\" height=\"107\" \/><\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>Items with imbuement slots can be imbued. Look at an item to see if it has any slots.<\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 93px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" width=\"265\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 267px;\">\n<p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/imbuing02.png\" width=\"267\" height=\"101\" \/><\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>Click on an imbuing shrine in a city temple and use it with an imbuable item to open the imbuing dialog.<\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 126px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" width=\"225\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 249px;\">\n<p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/imbuing03.png\" width=\"249\" height=\"138\" \/><\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>Depending on the item, different imbuements are available: elemental damage, elemental protection, skill and capacity boosts, critical hit, hit points leech, and mana leech.<\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 266px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 684px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 290.95px;\">\n<p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/imbuing04.png\" alt=\"button\" width=\"297\" height=\"194\" \/><\/p>\n<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 360.05px;\" align=\"left\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p>(1) Select one of the imbuements that are available for your item to see the required astral resources and gold.<\/p>\n<p>(2) Imbuing an item may not always succeed. You can bribe the fates with gold, though, to raise your success rate to 100%.<\/p>\n(3) If you have the required resources and gold, click the green arrow to imbue the item.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>Look at an imbued item or use an imbuing shrine with it to check the remaining time of an active imbuement.<\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 46px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" width=\"306\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 295px;\">\n<p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/imbuing05.png\" alt=\"button\" width=\"295\" height=\"36\" \/><\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>&nbsp;For most imbuements, time only decreases when the imbued item is equipped during combat.<\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 23px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" width=\"55\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 45px;\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/line1px.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"1\" \/><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>Imbuements vary not only in effect but also in power. <br \/>Get premium status to carry out intricate imbuements and unlock even more powerful imbuements through quests!<\/p>\n<\/center>","campaignid":0},{"index":0,"id":41,"publishdate":1512464400,"type":"regular","category":"major updates","headline":"<p>Winter Update 2017<\/p>","message":"<center>\n<table style=\"height: 88px;\" width=\"406\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 396px; vertical-align: top;\"><center>\n<p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/winter2017.jpg\" width=\"480\" height=\"380\" \/><\/p>\n<p>If you would like to find out more, check the <a href=\"http:\/\/www.tibia.com\/news\/?subtopic=newsarchive&amp;id=4389\">release news<\/a> on our website.<\/p>\n<\/center><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<\/center>","campaignid":0},{"index":1,"id":29,"publishdate":1500969600,"type":"regular","category":"major updates","headline":"<p>Summer Update 2017<\/p>","message":"<center>&nbsp; <img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/summer2017.jpg\" width=\"479\" height=\"379\" \/>\n<p>If you would like to find out more, check the <a href=\"http:\/\/www.tibia.com\/news\/?subtopic=newsarchive&amp;id=4169\">release news<\/a> on our website.<\/p>\n<p>Also, new Compendium entries have been added to explain the new features Daily Rewards, Analytics Tools, Quest Tracker, and Cyclopedia further.<\/p>\n<\/center>","campaignid":0},{"index":2,"id":21,"publishdate":1497016800,"type":"regular","category":"major updates","headline":"<p>Winter Update 2016<\/p>","message":"<center><table style=\"height: 88px;\" width=\"406\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 396px; vertical-align: top;\"><center><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/winter2016.jpg\" width=\"479\" height=\"379\" \/><\/p><p>If you would like to find out more, check the <a href=\"http:\/\/www.tibia.com\/news\/?subtopic=newsarchive&amp;id=3796\">release news<\/a> on our website.<\/p><\/center><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/center>","campaignid":0},{"index":3,"id":20,"publishdate":1497013200,"type":"regular","category":"major updates","headline":"<p>Summer Update 2016<\/p>","message":"<center><table style=\"height: 88px;\" width=\"406\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 396px; vertical-align: top;\"><center><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/summer2016.jpg\" width=\"479\" height=\"379\" \/><\/p><p>If you would like to find out more, check the <a href=\"http:\/\/www.tibia.com\/news\/?subtopic=newsarchive&amp;id=3600\">release news<\/a> on our website.<\/p><\/center><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/center>","campaignid":0},{"index":4,"id":19,"publishdate":1497009600,"type":"regular","category":"major updates","headline":"<p>Winter Update 2015<\/p>","message":"<center><table style=\"height: 88px;\" width=\"406\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 396px; vertical-align: top;\"><center><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/winter2015.jpg\" width=\"479\" height=\"379\" \/><\/p><p>If you would like to find out more, check the <a href=\"http:\/\/www.tibia.com\/news\/?subtopic=newsarchive&amp;id=3412\">release news<\/a> on our website.<\/p><\/center><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/center>","campaignid":0},{"index":5,"id":18,"publishdate":1497006000,"type":"regular","category":"major updates","headline":"<p>Summer Update 2015<\/p>","message":"<center><table style=\"height: 88px;\" width=\"406\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 396px; vertical-align: top;\"><center><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/summer2015.jpg\" width=\"479\" height=\"379\" \/><\/p><p>If you would like to find out more, check the <a href=\"http:\/\/www.tibia.com\/news\/?subtopic=newsarchive&amp;id=3244\">release news<\/a> on our website.<\/p><\/center><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/center>","campaignid":0},{"index":6,"id":17,"publishdate":1497002400,"type":"regular","category":"major updates","headline":"<p>Winter Update 2014<\/p>","message":"<center><table style=\"height: 88px;\" width=\"406\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 396px; vertical-align: top;\"><center><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/winter2014.jpg\" width=\"479\" height=\"379\" \/><\/p><p>If you would like to find out more, check the <a href=\"http:\/\/www.tibia.com\/news\/?subtopic=newsarchive&amp;id=3013\">release news<\/a> on our website.<\/p><\/center><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/center>","campaignid":0},{"index":7,"id":16,"publishdate":1496998800,"type":"regular","category":"major updates","headline":"<p>Summer Update 2014<\/p>","message":"<center><table style=\"height: 88px;\" width=\"406\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 396px; vertical-align: top;\"><center><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/summer2014.jpg\" width=\"479\" height=\"379\" \/><\/p><p>If you would like to find out more, check the <a href=\"http:\/\/www.tibia.com\/news\/?subtopic=newsarchive&amp;id=2809\">release news<\/a> on our website.<\/p><\/center><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/center>","campaignid":0},{"index":0,"id":32,"publishdate":1500951600,"type":"regular","category":"support","headline":"<p>Webshop<\/p>","message":"<center>In the Tibia Webshop you can order Premium Time, Tibia Coins or Extra Services for your account. Various payment methods are available <span class=\"st\">for your purchases<\/span>. <br \/> &nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/line1px.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"1\" \/><\/center><center>\n<p>Click <img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/manage_account.png\" vspace=\"1\" width=\"136\" height=\"27\" align=\"middle\" \/> on your account page to open your account management.<\/p>\n<p>Use the navigation bar or scroll down to go to the section <em>Products Available<\/em> from where you can access the Tibia Webshop or redeem a game code.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/webshop01.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"381\" height=\"55\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Click one of these three buttons to open the respective section of the Webshop:<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/webshop02.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"639\" height=\"251\" \/><\/p>\n<p>If no country is preselected or to change the selected country, please use the drop-down menu. All prices are shown in the currency of the country you have selected.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/webshop09.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"373\" height=\"53\" \/><\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 258px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 657px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 169.95px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p>(1) Click on one of the tabs to navigate through the Webshop and check which products are available.<\/p>\n<p>(2) Select the product you would like to purchase by clicking on it.<\/p>\n<p>Now you can see all payment methods you can use to purchase this product.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 455.05px;\" valign=\"middle\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/webshop10.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"391\" height=\"156\" \/><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>The price for the product you have selected may vary depending on the payment method you choose.<\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 200px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 490px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 287.867px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p>If you want to purchase Tibia Coins, you may notice that several payment methods are marked with two asterisks.<\/p>\n<p>If you use such a payment method, you will have to wait 6 months before you can trade the purchased Tibia Coins in the Market or gift them to other characters via the Store. Of course, you can use these Tibia Coins without delay to purchase products for your characters in the Store.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 170.133px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/webshop04.png\" width=\"169\" height=\"117\" \/><\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>Click <em>Next<\/em> to proceed once you have selected the product and payment method of your choice.<\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 174px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 635px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 198px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 381px; height: 198px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/webshop05.png\" width=\"381\" height=\"169\" \/><\/p>\n<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 222px; height: 198px;\" valign=\"middle\">You will now be asked to enter payment data depending on the payment method you selected. Hover over the question marks to get additional info about the data you need to enter.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>Click <em>Next<\/em> to proceed to the confirmation page. <br \/>All data you entered will be shown so please check it thoroughly.<\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 207px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 623px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 198px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 429px; height: 198px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/webshop11.png\" width=\"429\" height=\"251\" \/><\/p>\n<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 162px; height: 198px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p>(1) If everything has been entered correctly, check this box to accept the Extended Tibia Service Agreement and the Tibia Privacy Policy.<\/p>\n<p>(2) When you are ready to submit your order, click <em>Buy Now<\/em>.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>On the last page, you will receive a summary of your order and see whether or not your order was successful. Depending on the payment method you chose, you may also be provided with further instructions on how to complete your order (e.g. payment details for bank transfers, redirection to payment providers).<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>You bought a game code from one of our official resellers? Click the button <em>Use Game Code<\/em> in the section <em>Products Available<\/em> on your account management page to redeem it.<\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 202px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 637px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 198px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 202px; height: 198px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p>(1) Enter the 20-digit code. Make sure to enter all letters and numbers correctly.<\/p>\n<p>(2) Click <em>Next<\/em> to proceed. If you have entered a valid and correct game code, the code will be shown to you once more on the next page together with the service for which the game code is valid. If everything is correct, click <em>Next<\/em> again to activate the code.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 403px; height: 198px;\" valign=\"middle\">\n<p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/webshop08.png\" width=\"403\" height=\"183\" \/><\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<\/center>","campaignid":0},{"index":1,"id":27,"publishdate":1497362400,"type":"regular","category":"support","headline":"<p>The Store<\/p>","message":"<center>The Store offers a wide range of Tibia products that you can buy without having to leave the game.<\/center><center>Purchases are made with Tibia Coins, a special currency in Tibia.<br \/><table style=\"height: 23px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" width=\"55\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 45px;\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/line1px.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"1\" \/><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>Click on this button below your inventory to open the Store.<\/p><table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; height: 40px;\" width=\"123\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 107px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/store01.png\" width=\"107\" height=\"54\" \/><\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>&nbsp;You can check you current balance of Tibia Coins here:<\/p><table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; height: 255px;\" width=\"339\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 365px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/store02.png\" width=\"365\" height=\"283\" \/><\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>&nbsp;<br \/>Tibia Coins can be bought in our Webshop. Click this button to open the Tibia website in a browser window and log in to access the Webshop.<\/p><table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; height: 255px;\" width=\"339\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 365px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/store03.png\" width=\"365\" height=\"283\" \/><\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>You can also buy Tibia Coins from other players ingame via the Market.<\/p><p>&nbsp;<\/p><p>Browse through the categories to see the various products you can buy for Tibia Coins.<\/p><table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; height: 255px;\" width=\"339\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 365px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/store05.png\" width=\"365\" height=\"283\" \/><\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>&nbsp;<\/p><p>Hover over a product to read details about it. <br \/>If a Store product is greyed out, it is not available for your character. <br \/>Check the details of this product to find out why.<\/p><table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; height: 255px;\" width=\"339\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 365px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/store06.png\" width=\"479\" height=\"205\" \/><\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>&nbsp;<\/p><p>To buy something, select the product of your choice and click <em>Buy Now<\/em>. <br \/>Confirm your purchase by clicking <em>Buy<\/em> in the next window.<\/p><table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; height: 255px;\" width=\"339\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 365px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/store07.png\" width=\"617\" height=\"258\" \/><\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>&nbsp;<\/p><p>Check this box if you want to buy products instantly without any confirmation:<\/p><table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; height: 255px;\" width=\"339\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 365px;\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/store08.png\" width=\"383\" height=\"237\" \/><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>You can also change this setting via the General Options menu.<\/p><table style=\"height: 107px;\" width=\"263\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 255px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/store09.png\" width=\"255\" height=\"105\" \/><\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>&nbsp;<\/p><p>After a purchase, click this box to open it and close the window to continue.<\/p><table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; height: 112px;\" width=\"331\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 329px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/store10.png\" width=\"329\" height=\"147\" \/><\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>Portable items you have bought in the Store (e.g. potions) will be sent to your Store inbox.<br \/>You can open the Store inbox wherever you are.<\/p><table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; height: 210px; width: 651px;\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr style=\"height: 81px;\"><td style=\"width: 310.433px; height: 81px;\" valign=\"top\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/store11.png\" width=\"341\" height=\"167\" \/><\/p><\/td><td style=\"width: 307.567px; height: 81px;\" valign=\"middle\"><p>Items purchased in the Store can only be used by the character that purchased them.<\/p><p>Pieces of furniture or decoration bought in the Store can only be unwrapped in a house owned by this character.<\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>&nbsp;<\/p><p>You can also use the Store to gift Tibia Coins to other accounts. <br \/>You can only gift <a href=\"http:\/\/www.tibia.com\/support\/?subtopic=faq&amp;question=transferrequirements\">transferable Tibia Coins<\/a>.<\/p><table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; height: 112px;\" width=\"331\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 329px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/store12.png\" width=\"377\" height=\"304\" \/><\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>&nbsp;<\/p><p>Click <em>History<\/em> to see a history all of your Tibia Coins transactions.<\/p><table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; height: 255px;\" width=\"339\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 365px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/store04.png\" width=\"365\" height=\"283\" \/><\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/center>","campaignid":0},{"index":2,"id":25,"publishdate":1497279600,"type":"regular","category":"support","headline":"<p>Need Help?<\/p>","message":"<center>A wealth of information is available to help you find your way around in Tibia.<br \/><table style=\"height: 23px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" width=\"55\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 45px;\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/line1px.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"1\" \/><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>Hover your mouse cursor over a button or a bar in the client interface to have a tooltip appear.<\/p><table style=\"height: 38px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" width=\"224\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr style=\"height: 45px;\"><td style=\"width: 207px; height: 45px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/help01.png\" width=\"207\" height=\"47\" \/><\/p><\/td><td style=\"width: 207px; height: 45px;\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/help04.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"367\" height=\"55\" \/><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><br \/><p>Turn your mouse cursor into a magnifying glass by pressing <img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/help05.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"152\" height=\"42\" align=\"middle\" \/><\/p><table style=\"height: 205px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 498px;\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 370.983px;\"><p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/help02.png\" width=\"353\" height=\"159\" align=\"middle\" \/><\/p><\/td><td style=\"width: 95.0167px;\" valign=\"middle\">Now hover over certain elements of the client to get additional information displayed.<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>&nbsp;<\/p><p>You can also select the Help tab in the Options menu to get ingame help or to access specific help sections of the Tibia website.<\/p><table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; height: 213px;\" width=\"520\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 511px;\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/help03.png\" width=\"511\" height=\"246\" \/><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><table style=\"height: 23px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" width=\"55\" cellpadding=\"5\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 45px;\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/line1px.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"1\" \/><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><p>The <a href=\"http:\/\/www.tibia.com\/support\/?subtopic=gethelp\">Get Help<\/a> section on our website provides you with useful links to various topics related to the game itself and your account.<\/p><\/center>","campaignid":0},{"index":0,"id":42,"publishdate":1512050400,"type":"regular","category":"useful info","headline":"<p>Find Person on Optional PvP<\/p>","message":"<center>Decide&nbsp;who can locate your character&nbsp;with the Find Person spell \"exiva\" on Optional PvP worlds.<br \/>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/line1px.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"1\" \/>\n<table style=\"height: 202px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 749px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 198px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 33px; height: 198px; vertical-align: top;\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/exiva01.png\" width=\"227\" height=\"319\" \/><\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 484px; height: 198px; vertical-align: top;\">\n<p>Click on this icon above your chat console to open the Exiva Options dialog.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>Per default, only party and guild members are allowed to use the Find Person spell on you.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>This dialog allows you to customise your settings for the Find Person spell further.<\/p>\n<p>You can allow it for all characters, you can allow it for pre-defined groups and you can also set up whitelists to allow the spell for specific characters or guilds.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>Please note: if your guild participates in a guild war, all members of your guild, as well as the enemy guild will be able to use the Find Person spell on your character, regardless of your settings.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>To add characters to your whitelist, you can either enter their names via the text field in the dialog window (A) or you can directly add single character names via the context menu in your VIP list (B).<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/exiva02.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"583\" height=\"159\" \/><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>You can even set a hotkey via the hotkey menu to toggle between the option \"Allow all characters to use Exiva on me\" and your previous&nbsp;setting for the spell:<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/exiva03.png\" width=\"497\" height=\"92\" \/><\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 102px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 648px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 65px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 411px; height: 65px; vertical-align: middle;\">\n<p>If you use the spell on a character whom you are not allowed to locate, you will be notified in your server log.<\/p>\n<p>The regular amount of mana will still be consumed when casting the spell.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 205px; height: 65px; vertical-align: middle;\">\n<p><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/exiva04.png\" width=\"403\" height=\"90\" \/><\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<table style=\"height: 102px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 644px;\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 65px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 154.5px; height: 65px; vertical-align: middle;\"><img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/exiva05.png\" width=\"155\" height=\"43\" \/><\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 459.5px; height: 65px; vertical-align: middle;\">\n<p>If someone uses the spell on you but is not allowed to locate you, a quick glow of the Exiva Options icon will inform you about the attempt.<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<\/center>","campaignid":0},{"index":1,"id":37,"publishdate":1506682800,"type":"regular","category":"useful info","headline":"<p>Premium Features<\/p>","message":"<center>Get premium status to enjoy exclusive abilities and advantages inside and outside the game.<br \/>&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/line1px.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"1\" \/>\n<p>Treat yourself to Premium Time to access everything listed here:<\/p>\n<div style=\"vertical-align: middle;\">\n<table style=\"height: 231px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 566px;\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"2\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 15px;\">\n<th style=\"width: 134px; height: 15px;\">Benefit<\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 123.033px; height: 15px;\">Premium Details<\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 144.967px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;Free<\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 134px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;Premium<\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"width: 134px; height: 15px; text-align: center;\">XP boost<\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 123.033px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/premiumicon_stamina.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"35\" height=\"34\" \/><\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 144.967px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;0<\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 134px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;+50%<\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"width: 134px; height: 15px;\">Offline training<\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 123.033px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/premiumicon_trainingstatues.png\" width=\"35\" height=\"34\" \/><\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 144.967px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/premiumicon_no.png\" width=\"15\" height=\"14\" \/><\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 134px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/premiumicon_yes.png\" width=\"15\" height=\"11\" \/><\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"width: 134px; height: 15px;\">Refined quick looting<\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 123.033px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/premiumicon_quickloot.png\" width=\"35\" height=\"34\" \/><\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 144.967px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/premiumicon_no.png\" width=\"15\" height=\"14\" \/><\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 134px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/premiumicon_yes.png\" width=\"15\" height=\"11\" \/><\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"width: 134px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;Areas<\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 123.033px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/premiumicon_newareas.png\" width=\"35\" height=\"34\" \/><\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 144.967px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;5 areas and cities<\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 134px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;17+ areas and cities<\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"width: 134px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;Spells<\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 123.033px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/premiumicon_spells.png\" width=\"35\" height=\"34\" \/><\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 144.967px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;55<\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 134px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;139+<\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"width: 134px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;Instant travelling<\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 123.033px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/premiumicon_travel.png\" width=\"35\" height=\"34\" \/><\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 144.967px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/premiumicon_no.png\" width=\"15\" height=\"14\" \/><\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 134px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/premiumicon_yes.png\" width=\"15\" height=\"11\" \/><\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"width: 134px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;Outfit<\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 123.033px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/premiumicon_outfit.png\" width=\"35\" height=\"34\" \/><\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 144.967px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;4<\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 134px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;32+<\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"width: 134px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;Mounts<\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 123.033px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/premiumicon_mount.png\" width=\"35\" height=\"34\" \/><\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 144.967px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;3 (rentable)<\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 134px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;41+<\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"width: 134px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;Death penalty<\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 123.033px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/premiumicon_death.png\" width=\"35\" height=\"34\" \/><\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 144.967px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;0% reduction<\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 134px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;30% reduction<\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"width: 134px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;Market offers<\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 123.033px; height: 15px;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"http:\/\/static.tibia.com\/images\/news\/premiumicon_market.png\" width=\"35\" height=\"34\" \/><\/th>\n<th style=\"width: 144.9